---
// src/pages/transparency.astro
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import NavBlock from "../components/NavBlock.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="AI Transparency | Quirgs"
  description="How Quirgs uses AI — disclosure of AI-generated content, AI-assisted development, and platform governance posture."
  terminalPath="~/transparency"
>
  <NavBlock currentPath="/transparency/" />

  <div class="line">
    <span class="prompt">admin@quirgs</span><span class="path"
      >~/transparency</span
    ><span class="text-bright">$</span>&nbsp;cat transparency.md
  </div>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <div class="detail-header">
    <h1 class="text-bright">AI Transparency Notice</h1>
    <p class="tagline">
      How Quirgs uses AI — content, development, and governance.
    </p>
  </div>

  <p>
    Quirgs is a platform for building AI products responsibly. This page
    discloses how Quirgs uses AI in its own operations — content production,
    platform development, and skills delivery.
  </p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <h2 class="text-bright">AI-Generated Content</h2>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    The Quirgs YouTube channel produces educational content on building AI
    products responsibly. Scripts, voiceover, presentation slides, and Shorts
    are produced with AI assistance. The tools in use include Claude (scripting
    and narration drafts), Remotion (slide and motion asset composition), Google
    Vids (voiceover), and Veo (cinematic b-roll).
  </p>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    All AI-generated video content published by Quirgs will carry explicit
    transparency labels. This labeling practice is being aligned with EU AI Act
    Omnibus VII requirements ahead of the effective date. Human review and
    approval is applied at every stage — topic selection, scripting, asset
    review, and final publish decision — before any content reaches the channel.
  </p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <h2 class="text-bright">AI-Assisted Platform Development</h2>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    The quirgs.com site and the skills it distributes were built with AI coding
    assistance. Development tools include Claude Cowork and Claude Code (prompt
    assistance, component and logic generation, bug fixes, integration
    assistance), Gemini via Antigravity (scaffolding and integration), and Jules
    (build validation). All structural decisions — architecture, component
    design, content, and navigation — are human-reviewed and approved before any
    code merges to the integration branch or deploys to production.
  </p>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    No code or content change reaches quirgs.com without explicit human sign-off
    at a defined checkpoint in the development workflow.
  </p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <h2 class="text-bright">Skills Advisory Disclaimer</h2>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    The compliance skills in the Quirgs bundle — eu-ai-act-classifier,
    nist-ai-rmf-checkpoint, iso-42001-audit-prep, hitl-compliance-gate,
    ai-transparency-writer, pii-exposure-checker, and incident-response-logger —
    are governance support tools. They produce structured analysis, checklists,
    and draft documents to support compliance work.
  </p>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    They are not legal advice. They are not a substitute for qualified legal
    counsel, a licensed compliance professional, or a certified auditor with
    jurisdiction-specific expertise. Every skill carries this disclaimer
    explicitly in its output. Use them to accelerate governance work — not to
    replace the professional judgment and review that compliance decisions
    require.
  </p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <h2 class="text-bright">Platform Governance Posture</h2>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    Quirgs governs its own AI use through the same three-pillar framework it
    teaches: Inventory, Checkpoints, and Standards Alignment.
  </p>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    <span class="text-bright">Inventory.</span> Every AI tool in use at Quirgs — in
    content production, site development, and skills delivery — is documented. We
    maintain a current record of which AI systems are in use, their roles, and their
    scope.
  </p>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    <span class="text-bright">Checkpoints.</span> Human-in-the-loop review gates are
    applied at every stage where AI output influences a decision or a published deliverable.
    No AI-generated content, code, or skill output advances without explicit human
    approval.
  </p>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    <span class="text-bright">Standards Alignment.</span> Quirgs tracks obligations
    under the EU AI Act, NIST AI RMF, and ISO/IEC 42001 and applies relevant controls
    to its own operations. The compliance bundle distributed by Quirgs was used in
    building and governing this platform.
  </p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <h2 class="text-bright">Release Provenance</h2>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    The platform is versioned with calendar-based releases (<span class="text-bright"
    >YYYY.MM</span>), tagged in the public repository and published as GitHub
    Releases. Each release compiles the changelog entries for everything merged
    that month, including skill and bundle version bumps — nothing ships
    untracked. The full feed:
  </p>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    <a href="https://github.com/unqdlphn/quirgs/releases"
      >github.com/unqdlphn/quirgs/releases</a
    >
  </p>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <p>
    Skill and bundle versions shown on <a href="/skills/">/skills/</a> are not
    hand-maintained — they derive at build time from the same plugin manifests
    the install commands fetch, and a scheduled integrity check verifies the
    live site and registry against those manifests. Releases close that loop:
    the version you see, the version you install, and the version in the release
    notes are the same number by construction.
  </p>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <div>
    Questions? See <a href="/support/">/support/</a>.
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
